sourceQuestion:
Consider the following context-free grammar over the alphabet {a, b, c} with S as the start symbol:
S -> abScT | abcT
T -> bT | b

Which one of the following represents the language generated by the above grammar?
A. {(ab)^n (cb^n)^n | n >= 1}
B. {(ab)^n c(b^n_1 c)(b^n_2 c)...(b^n_n c) | n >= 1, n_1, n_2, ..., n_n >= 1}
C. {(ab)^n (cb^m)^n | m, n >= 1}
D. {(ab)^n cb^n | n >= 1}

Identify the language generated by the following grammar, where S is the start variable.

S -> XY
X -> aX | a
Y -> aYb | epsilon

A. {a^m b^n | m >= n, n >= 0}
B. {a^m b^n | m > n, n >= 0}
C. {a^m b^n | m >= n, n >= 0}
D. {a^m b^n | m > n, n >= 0}

Which one of the following languages over Sigma = {a, b} is NOT context-free?

A. {ww^R | w in {a, b}^*}
B. {wa^n b^n w^R | w in {a, b}^*, n >= 0}
C. {wa^n b^n w^R | w in {a, b}^*, n >= 0}
D. {a^i b^j c^k | i, j, k in {3n, 5n | n >= 0}}
